    comments: "Helps paint the victims of John Doe"
  }
  pacing: "Pacing is good as tension really makes this movie feel like this movie is moving at the right speed"
  climax: "Climax is brilliant as it is one of the most iconic endings in all of cinema history; the very last scene seems a bit unnecessary because they should've just ended the movie in the climax"
  tone: "Tone is very much a serial-killer crime thriller"
  final_notes: ""
  overall: "Overall, a great movie that is carried by its incredible writing and great filmmaking as David Fincher creates an grimey serial-killer thriller that is his coming out party to the cinematic world"
